-- FACTBOX-Carlsberg, Metro among European companies most exposed to Russia
-- 
-- Fri Mar 21, 2014 08:20AM EDT
-- None



March 21 (Reuters) - Finnish tyre maker Nokian Renkaat <NRE1V.HE>, Austrian lender Raiffeisen Bank International <RBIV.VI> Danish brewer Carlsberg <CARLb.CO> and German retailer Metro <MEOG.DE> feature among the European blue-chips with the biggest exposure to Russia, data from index provider MSCI shows.

Germany's main trade body has warned that if an escalation of Europe's stand-off with Moscow over Crimea results in economic sanctions, more than 6,000 German companies which do business with Russia would suffer "catastrophic losses". [ID:nL6N0MI1ID] The United States and European Union on Thursday added names to their lists of individuals targeted by sanctions. Below is a table of the 100 European listed companies with the biggest exposure to Russia, in terms of percentage of overall revenues, according to MSCI data.